    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a94ce51e_c2b5fcae",
        "filename": "cq/api/bigquery/attempt.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003190
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-20T20:05:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The thing that\u0027s unclear to me is: if it \"didn\u0027t permanently fail\" and Gerrit rejected it, e.g. due to the CQ being out of quota, does this mean the submission is going to be retried?\n\nThese values are sent went an attempt is removed, and so everything is the final state. It seems to me like if CQ tried and knows the submission was not successful, and the attempt is being removed, then it could just be FAILURE?\n\nAre we trying to separate \"failure because Gerrit rejected the submission because the change can\u0027t be submitted\", and \"failure even though the change should be submittable there was a quota error etc.\"? -- Would it be overkill to add more values here, like some kind of INFRA_FAILURE, or QUOTA_FAILURE?",
      "parentUuid": "3ea96c8e_83b846c1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 72,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 72,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "8d3e41b8a077e7deb28ac3c5b6a66a69254117cb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0205f642_bdbfc228",
        "filename": "cq/api/bigquery/attempt.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-20T20:32:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good thinking. The actual case when this happens is:\n\n1. Attempt passed all verifiers, it\u0027s added to _ready_attempts.\n2. Submitter thread starts working on it, tries to submit first CL, but during each of 5 tries gets:\n  a) 500 for submit but is able to refresh change status and verify it wasn\u0027t submitted\n  b) 429 quota error\n3. Submitter thread stops working on it, for now, leaving attempt in _ready_attempts and taking some other attempt (it\u0027s random) from the the _ready_attempts.\n4. Meanwhile, something changes s.t. CQ decides to stop working on this CL entirely; for example:\n  a) ABORTED case: user removes CQ+2\n  b) FAILED case: reviewer removes CR+1, gerrit_cqability verifier fails attempt.\n  c) FAILED case: user loses membership in committers group, gerrit_cqability verifier fails attempt.\n  etc\n5. CQ removes attempt from consideration and from submitter\u0027s thread _ready_attempts.\n\n\nThe 12a34a5 actually happened, and 4a/4b are quire frequent on their own, too.\n\nNote, however, that from perspective of someone querying attempts table and checking CL submit status all that matters is that they can treat \n\n  status\u003d\u0027UNSPECIFIED\u0027 as if CQ never tried submitting in the first place.\n\nIf it helps, I\u0027d rather get rid of this confusing addition entirely - but I think you could perhaps suggest less confusing phrasing?",
      "parentUuid": "a94ce51e_c2b5fcae",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 72,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 72,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "8d3e41b8a077e7deb28ac3c5b6a66a69254117cb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e514d09d_a87dffec",
        "filename": "cq/api/bigquery/attempt.proto",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003190
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-20T22:12:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What about calling it \"PENDING\"? In both case (1) not tried at all yet, and (2) tried once, and then removed before retry for other reasons, you could say it\u0027s \"pending\" a submit try.\n\nI think you\u0027d want to still keep the comment as-is, though.",
      "parentUuid": "0205f642_bdbfc228",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 72,
        "startChar": 35,
