      "writtenOn": "2019-12-20T20:05:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree that SUBMIT_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED is very long and cumbersome, and would make queries longer if used in queries. But if it\u0027s just the default value that\u0027s never explicitly used, then queries in general won\u0027t need to use this value, right?\n\nhttps://cloud.google.com/apis/design/naming_convention#enum_names suggests that the default value \"should\" be ..._UNSPECIFIED and would be used when a value is not specified... so it could be used as a value meaning \"CQ unexpectedly didn\u0027t fill in a value for the data, even though it should have filled in a value\".\n\n(This is just a suggestion though)",
