      "writtenOn": "2019-12-20T20:05:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Makes sense.\n\nTo me, at first, \"presumably\" sort of sounds like \"we don\u0027t know, but we\u0027re assuming...\" and indeed in many cases you don\u0027t know whether errors are transient or not. Another alternative might be \"probably transient\", but \"presumably\" is at least as good.",
